cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on semantic role labeling (SRL), which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning method using neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of LSTM, which is a type of neural network, and thus, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses syntactic constraints to improve SRL performance, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as syntactic analysis is also used in image processing.
